<li><a href="http://worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n79-21164" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n79-21164" rel="nofollow">Works by or about Mark Twain</a> in libraries (<a href="/wiki/WorldCat" title="WorldCat">WorldCat</a> catalog)</li>
<li><a href="http://docsouth.unc.edu/neh/twain/menu.html" class="external text" title="http://docsouth.unc.edu/neh/twain/menu.html" rel="nofollow">A True Story, Repeated Word for Word As I Heard It. From The Atlantic Monthly. Nov. 1874: 591-594.</a> Boston: Atlantic Monthly Co., November 1874. Boston: Atlantic Monthly Co., November 1874.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.booksinmyphone.com/index.php?author=Mark%20Twain" class="external text" title="http://www.booksinmyphone.com/index.php?author=Mark%20Twain" rel="nofollow">Free to read on a cell phone</a> - Twain works.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.quotes-famous.com/person/Mark-Twain-quotes.html" class="external text" title="http://www.quotes-famous.com/person/Mark-Twain-quotes.html" rel="nofollow">Mark Twain Quotes</a></li>
<li><a href="http://twainquotes.com/" class="external text" title="http://twainquotes.com/" rel="nofollow">Mark Twain Quotes, Newspaper Collections and Related Resources</a></li>
<li>Full text of <a href="http://searchwithin.org/journal/tat_journal-13.html#7" class="external text" title="http://searchwithin.org/journal/tat_journal-13.html#7" rel="nofollow"><i>My Platonic Sweetheart</i></a> , a dream journal by Mark Twain</li>
<li><a href="http://www.oldfashionedamericanhumor.com/punch-brothers-punch.html" class="external text" title="http://www.oldfashionedamericanhumor.com/punch-brothers-punch.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Punch, Brothers, Punch!</i></a> – text of this famous work</li>
<li><a href="http://essays.quotidiana.org/twain/" class="external text" title="http://essays.quotidiana.org/twain/" rel="nofollow">Essays by Mark Twain at Quotidiana.org</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.crossmyt.com/hc/linghebr/awfgrmlg.html" class="external text" title="http://www.crossmyt.com/hc/linghebr/awfgrmlg.html" rel="nofollow">Twain on The Awful German Language</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.animalrightshistory.org/twa_mark-twain/scientific-research.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.animalrightshistory.org/twa_mark-twain/scientific-research.htm" rel="nofollow">Mark Twain on Scientific Research / Pains of Lowly Life</a> (1900)</li>
<li><a href="http://librivox.org/newcatalog/search.php?title=&amp;author=mark+twain&amp;status=all&amp;action=Search" class="external text" title="http://librivox.org/newcatalog/search.php?title=&amp;author=mark+twain&amp;status=all&amp;action=Search" rel="nofollow">Audiobooks of Twain's Writings</a> from <a href="/wiki/Librivox" title="Librivox" class="mw-redirect">Librivox</a></li>
</ul>
<dl>
<dt>Academic studies</dt>
</dl>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://bancroft.berkeley.edu/MTP/" class="external text" title="http://bancroft.berkeley.edu/MTP/" rel="nofollow">The Mark Twain Papers and Project of the Bancroft Library, University of California Berkeley</a>. Home to the largest archive of Mark Twain's papers and the editors of a critical edition of all of his writings.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.buffalolib.org/libraries/collections/index.asp?sec=twain" class="external text" title="http://www.buffalolib.org/libraries/collections/index.asp?sec=twain" rel="nofollow">Buffalo Library</a> Mark Twain Room, which houses the manuscript of <i>Huckleberry Finn</i></li>
<li><a href="http://www.ucpress.edu/books/twain.html" class="external text" title="http://www.ucpress.edu/books/twain.html" rel="nofollow">The University of California Press</a><sup class="noprint Inline-Template"><span title="&#160;since November 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Dead_external_links" title="Wikipedia:Dead external links">dead link</a></i>]</span></sup> Publishers of the critical edition of Mark Twain's writings.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.elmira.edu/academics/ar_marktwain.shtml" class="external text" title="http://www.elmira.edu/academics/ar_marktwain.shtml" rel="nofollow">Elmira College Center for Mark Twain Studies</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.marxists.de/culture/twain/noteach.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.marxists.de/culture/twain/noteach.htm" rel="nofollow">"The Mark Twain they didn’t teach us about in school"</a>, by Helen Scott, from <i><a href="/wiki/International_Socialist_Review" title="International Socialist Review">International Socialist Review</a></i> 10, Winter 2000, pp.61-65.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.hrc.utexas.edu/research/fa/lfclemens.html" class="external text" title="http://www.hrc.utexas.edu/research/fa/lfclemens.html" rel="nofollow">Mark Twain Collection</a> at the <a href="/wiki/Harry_Ransom_Center" title="Harry Ransom Center" class="mw-redirect">Harry Ransom Center</a> at the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Texas_at_Austin" title="University of Texas at Austin">University of Texas at Austin</a></li>
</ul>
